#
# Semgrep exclusion list for legacy main-line code on next/v1.
#
# Why this file exists.
# ---------------------
# next/v1 carries forward the main-line PoC code (Dockerfile, FastAPI
# server, Open WebUI patches, embedded skills) so the branch stays
# buildable while the enterprise architecture is designed. That legacy
# code does not pass the Layer 0 SAST gate — it has root-running
# containers, wildcard CORS, md5 cache keys, stdlib XML parsing, etc.
# None of it is shipped in the v1 GA architecture: every component is
# rewritten from scratch under docs/architecture/ in Layer 6+, and each
# new component PR removes its path from this file in the same commit.
#
# Policy: docs/architecture/adr/0001-layer-0-gate-legacy-exclusion.md
# Process: docs/architecture/PROCESS.md ("Adding a component" step 4)
#
# Rules for editing this file.
# ----------------------------
# 1. Adding a path requires an ADR amendment. Do not silently add
#    exclusions to make a finding go away.
# 2. Removing a path is mandatory in the same PR that introduces a
#    new-architecture component covering that area. CI must pass
#    without the exclusion before the PR can merge.
# 3. New code (anything under docs/architecture/ proper, .github/,
#    helm/ once rewritten, future components/) is NEVER excluded.

# --- Legacy main-line code ---------------------------------------------------

# Sandbox image — root-running, sudo usage, dynamic urllib. Replaced by the
# Sandbox Runtime component (Layer 6+, Kata + Cloud Hypervisor per BoM #5).
Dockerfile

# MCP orchestrator FastAPI service — wildcard CORS, md5 keys, stdlib XML.
# Replaced by the Control Plane + Session Lifecycle components.
computer-use-server/

# Open WebUI integration — runs as root in container, no USER directive.
# Replaced by an external IdP-driven UI integration (not bundled in v1 GA).
openwebui/

# Settings sidecar — root container. Folded into Control Plane in Layer 6+.
settings-wrapper/

# Cleanup cron container — root, sudo. Folded into k8s-native lifecycle
# (Kyverno + controller) in Layer 6+.
cron/
cleanup/

# Bundled-skills PoC code — defused-xml gaps, file-perms issues. v1 ships
# zero default skills (per manifesto/04-non-goals.md); SkillProvider stays
# TBD. These directories will be deleted, not refactored. Both
# `skills/public/` and `skills/examples/` are out of scope: v1 GA does
# not bundle any skill, the directories die together.
skills/public/pptx/
skills/public/docx/
skills/public/webapp-testing/
skills/examples/

# Main-line Helm chart release workflow — pre-existing run-shell-injection
# on its `gh release` step. Replaced by the Layer 6+ release workflow once
# the supply-chain.yml pattern is extended to chart artifacts.
.github/workflows/release-chart.yml

# Main-line test code — stdlib XML parsing in PoC test fixtures. New
# components ship their own tests under each component's directory;
# this top-level `tests/` tree dies as the legacy code does.
tests/

# --- Not legacy, just out of scope for SAST ---------------------------------

# Vendored third-party research repos. Not part of any release artifact.
references/
vendor/

# In-progress architecture buffer. Prose, not source. Migrated to
# docs/architecture/ over time.
docs/future-architecture/

# Planning cache, never executed.
.planning/
